OL,3,CLabour to look into law supporting
OL,4,Cparents of critically ill children
OL,6,FUnder current law, parents of newborn
OL,7,Fbabies who become unwell within the
OL,8,Ffirst 28 days of life are entitled to
OL,9,Fpaid leave and job protection to be by
OL,10,Ftheir child's bedside.
OL,12,FHowever, if their child is diagnosed
OL,13,Fwith cancer at 29 days old, the
OL,14,Fparents no longer have the right to
OL,15,Ffinancial support.
OL,17,FCeri and Frances say the situation
OL,18,Fmeans there is a "cruel gap in
OL,19,Fsupport", not based on the severity of
OL,20,Fa child's illness but the date they
OL,21,Fare diagnosed.
